  <title xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support for NGOs to Sahel, 2012 - Caritas/DRC/DCA/Save the Children</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Projektet bidrager til at d&#xE6;kke de umiddelbare behov for f&#xF8;devarer og vand blandt 5.134 Mali-flygtninge og s&#xE5;rbare v&#xE6;rtsfamilier i Tillab&#xE9;ry-regionen i Niger. 100 s&#xE5;rbare, lokale beboere f&#xE5;r hj&#xE6;lp til dyrkning af gr&#xF8;ntsager. Sundhedsklinikken i Ayourou f&#xE5;r medicinforsyninger til at sikre flygtningene adgang til basale sundhedsydelser.
Red Barnet; In Mali 19.510 children and 7225 adults affected by the conflict and food crisis were ensured access to education, protection, basic healthcare, food, water and sanitation. Furthermore, support was provided to the coordination of the Education Cluster. The project was delayed due to the unstable situation in Mali. 
In Burkina Faso 900 young people in the refugee camp Gandafabou received access to informal and formal education in a protected environment.</narrative>
